HEADWORD: Chambermaid
<hw>Cham"ber*maid`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
maidservant who has the care of chambers, making the beds, sweeping,
cleaning the rooms, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lady's maid.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chambertin</ent>⟦br⟧
